body: "## Charter\nCapability epic for concurrency & multi-agent safety, created from the 2026-07-03 concurrency audit. pm is agent-first: many agents mutate one git-backed workspace in parallel, so locking, claim semantics, id allocation, and singleton-file writes must be safe by construction. Audit verdict: data integrity held under all parallel stress (no corruption, no history drift) — the five children are availability/atomicity gaps, not corruption bugs.\n\n## Delivery order (dependency-informed)\n1. pm-2muu lock-wait retry (in progress, implemented uncommitted) — foundation: gives every mutation a bounded wait.\n2. pm-8t5x claim test-and-set (in progress, implemented uncommitted) — relies on the item lock; with 2muu it is a true atomic test-and-set.\n3. pm-zwib stale-lock takeover race — related to 2muu (its removal cap bounds but does not fix the race).\n4. pm-khdq create/copy ID allocation TOCTOU (silent item overwrite — worst blast radius).\n5. pm-bgcu singleton-file (settings/schema/session/checkpoints) lock-free read-modify-write.\n\n## Verification bar\nEvery child closes with parallel-stress evidence recorded via pm test / notes (the audit's empirical repros re-run green): N-parallel mutations self-heal, claims are exclusive, no lost config writes, no id collisions."
